
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh` baraye rahandazi Docker be soorate bi-niaz az root (rootless) rooye system-haye Linux estefade mishavad. In dastoor Docker ra be goone'i config mikonad ke yek karbare mamooli (non-root user) ham betavanad az Docker estefade konad.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh install`  --> 🚀 Docker ra be soorate rootless nasb mikonad.
    🔹 `dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh uninstall` --> 🗑️ Docker rootless ra hazf mikonad.
    🔹 `dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh status`    --> ℹ️ Vaziyat Docker rootless ra neshon midahad.
    🔹 `dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh help`      --> ❓ Rahnamaye kamel dastoor ra neshon midahad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh install

    🔹 Docker ra be soorate rootless nasb mikonad. Az shoma password khaste mishavad, pas az vard kardane password karbare shoma be group docker ezafe mishavad.

    $ dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh uninstall

    🔹 Docker rootless ra az system hazf mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh status

    🔹 Agar Docker be dorosti nasb shode bashad, etela'ati dar morede vaziyat-e an neshon midahad. Dar gheire in soorat, peyghami مبنی bar nasb nashodan Docker neshon midahad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh` command is used to set up Docker to run in rootless mode on Linux systems.  This allows a regular (non-root) user to use Docker without requiring root privileges.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh install`  --> 🚀 Installs Docker in rootless mode.
    🔹 `dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh uninstall` --> 🗑️ Uninstalls Docker rootless.
    🔹 `dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh status`    --> ℹ️ Shows the status of Docker rootless.
    🔹 `dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh help`      --> ❓ Shows the complete command help.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh install

    🔹 Installs Docker in rootless mode. You will be prompted for your password, after which your user is added to the docker group.

    $ dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh uninstall

    🔹 Removes Docker rootless from the system.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh status

    🔹 If Docker is installed correctly, it shows information about its status.  Otherwise, it displays a message indicating that Docker is not installed.
